volunteer_experiences.description:
MINIONU is a project carried out by the Department of International Relations at PUC Minas that aims to bring international themes to high school students. It is part of a set of United Nations simulations carried out around the world. It is a pedagogical project with a comprehensive concept of learning. The project is capable of transforming realities by empowering the voices of youth. 
- Responsible for coordinate the work in its respective committee throughout the year and on MINIONU days;
Participate in training sessions on rules throughout the school year; Promote the MINIONU through institutionalized channels and in the appropriate manner; 
To disseminate, nationally and internationally, the purposes of the project; To promote integration among the members of its team (assistant directors and volunteers) and between them and the other members of the 19th MINIONU team;
